1. J. P. Gordon, H. J. Zeiger, and C. H. Townes, "Molecular microwave oscillator and new hyperfine structure in the microwave spectrum of NH$_3$," *Phys. Rev.*, vol. 95, pp. 282-284; July 1, 1954. "The maser-new type of microwave amplifier, frequency standard, and spectrometer," *Phys. Rev.*, vol. 99, pp. 1264-1274; August 15, 1955.
2. M. W. Muller, "Noise in a molecular amplifier," *Phys. Rev.*, vol. 106, pp. 8-12; April 1, 1957.
3. J. P. Gordon and L. D. White, "Noise in maser amplifiers-theory and experiment," *PROC. IRE*, vol. 46, pp. 1599-1594; September, 1958.
4. K. Shimoda, T. C. Wang, and C. H. Townes, "Further aspects of maser theory," *Phys. Rev.*, vol. 102, pp. 1308-1321; June 1, 1956.
